{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e0323929-890c-4265-8490-0dc6ea95b29e","content":"There's no existing pipeline file in this directory. Here's a concise guide for migrating from `VSTest@3` to `Microsoft.Testing.Platform` while keeping TRX reports and code coverage:\n\n### Key changes\n\n**1. Replace `VSTest@3` with `DotNetCoreCLI@2` (or a plain `dotnet test` script):**\n\n```yaml\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run tests'\n  inputs:\n    command: test\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >\n      --configuration Release\n      --logger \"trx;LogFileName=results.trx\"\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n      --collect \"Code Coverage\"\n```\n\n**2. Enable Microsoft.Testing.Platform in your test projects:**\n\nAdd to each test `.csproj` (or `Directory.Build.props`):\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nThe `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property lets `dotnet test` drive the new runner (so the CLI task above still works).\n\n**3. Publish results & coverage (unchanged):**\n\n```yaml\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: VSTest\n    testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.cobertura.xml'\n```\n\n### Why not `VSTest@3`?\n\n`VSTest@3` invokes `vstest.console`, which doesn't understand the new `Microsoft.Testing.Platform` executable model. `dotnet test` with `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` bridges the gap, keeping the familiar CLI while using the new runner under the hood.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"84c28ed6-8ede-400a-9490-e81deda492ff","outputTokens":499,"requestId":"3408:9F564:5903DDF:61191FF:69F3FB1C"},"id":"6394c27f-6791-42c5-924b-4acb1a9250bf","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:00:22.974Z","parentId":"f449362d-7067-4d24-b5ad-d3410ccc6f2f"}
